      • getVertexForEClassRaw

        public static org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.structure.Vertex getVertexForEClassRaw(org.chronos.chronograph.api.structure.ChronoGraph graph,
                                                                                  org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EClass eClass)
        Attempts to find the Vertex that represents the given EClass in the graph.

        In contrast to getVertexForEClass(ChronoEPackageRegistry, ChronoGraph, EClass), this method does not rely on IDs, but rather on the graph structure itself and on the name of the EClass.

        This method should not be used outside of a package initialization process!

        Parameters:
        graph - The graph to search in. Must not be null.
        eClass - The EClass to search the vertex for. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The vertex that represents the given EClass, or null if no vertex is found.
